            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "We're already importing python modules without the extension, that's the whole source of your issue, you've chosen a non-standard extension that instead looks like an import path. How do we distinguish `import app.wsgi` from `python app.wsgi` when only given the string `app.wsgi`?\r\n\r\nThe much, much simpler solution is for you to name Python files with the standard `.py` extension. `app.py` and `wsgi.py` are even autodetected, so you don't need to specify `FLASK_APP` in that case."
